CSS workflow

Preprocessors - sass, less, stylus. These let us save variables in CSS which we normally can't, or writing nested CSS because browsers don't support it. These processors convert it to regular CSS.

PostCSS is the trendy new one apparently, but it's also the fastest.

Vocab Building

gulp lets us automatically do this.

gulp.src pulls the source, gulp.dest is the destination. IN between we can run a PostCSS filter

Block Element Modifier - way more clear, 1:1 relationship with html and styling 
